From: Yifei Sun <ysun@hey.com>
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] drm/vc4: remove duplicate drm_connector_hdmi_audio_init() call

Commit c0317ad44f45 ("drm/vc4: fix infinite EPROBE_DEFER loop") moved
drm_connector_hdmi_audio_init() out of vc4_hdmi_connector_init() and
into vc4_hdmi_audio_init(), so that the codec platform device (a child
of the HDMI controller) is registered only after the deferring call to
devm_snd_dmaengine_pcm_register().

Merge commit 45215c589e7f ("Merge tag 'drm-misc-next-2025-06-12' of
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/misc/kernel into drm-next") combined
drm-misc-next (which had the fix) with drm-next (which still had the
original call). The merge resolution kept both copies, leaving a stale
call in vc4_hdmi_connector_init() in addition to the intended one in
vc4_hdmi_audio_init().

drm_connector_hdmi_audio_init() is not idempotent: each call invokes
platform_device_register_data() with PLATFORM_DEVID_AUTO, registering a
fresh hdmi-audio-codec platform device. The second call overwrites
connector->hdmi_audio.codec_pdev, leaking the first device. It also
re-introduces the EPROBE_DEFER hazard that c0317ad44f45 addressed,
because the connector_init call adds a child device before
vc4_hdmi_audio_init() runs (and may defer).

Drop the duplicate so only the post-defer call in vc4_hdmi_audio_init()
remains.

Fixes: 45215c589e7f ("Merge tag 'drm-misc-next-2025-06-12' of https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/misc/kernel into drm-next")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Yifei Sun <ysun@hey.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c | 6 ------
 1 file changed, 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c
@@ -554,12 +554,6 @@ static int vc4_hdmi_connector_init(struct drm_device *dev,
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;

-	ret = drm_connector_hdmi_audio_init(connector, dev->dev,
-					    &vc4_hdmi_audio_funcs,
-					    8, 0, false, -1);
-	if (ret)
-		return ret;
-
 	drm_connector_helper_add(connector, &vc4_hdmi_connector_helper_funcs);

 	/*
